4 A JOINT RESOLUTION OF THE SENATE AND THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE STATE OF
5 MONTANA APPLYING FOR A CONVENTION OF THE STATES UNDER ARTICLE V OF THE
6 CONSTITUTION OF THE UNITED STATES.
7
8 WHEREAS, the founders of our Constitution empowered state legislators to be guardians of liberty
9 against future abuses of power by the federal government; and
10 WHEREAS, the federal government has created a crushing national debt through improper and
11 imprudent spending; and
12 WHEREAS, the federal government has invaded the legitimate roles of the states through the
13 manipulative process of federal mandates, most of which are unfunded to a great extent; and
14 WHEREAS, the federal government has ceased to live under a proper interpretation of the Constitution
15 of the United States; and
16 WHEREAS, it is the solemn duty of the states to protect the liberty of our people -- particularly for the
17 generations to come -- by proposing amendments to the Constitution of the United States through a convention
18 of the states under Article V for the purpose of restraining these and related abuses of power.
19
20 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE AND THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF
21 THE STATE OF MONTANA:
22 Section 1. The Legislature of the State of Montana hereby applies to Congress, under the
23 provisions of Article V of the Constitution of the United States, for the calling of a convention of the states
24 limited to proposing amendments to the Constitution of the United States that impose fiscal restraints on the
25 federal government, limit the power and jurisdiction of the federal government, and limit the terms of office for
26 its officials and for members of Congress.
27 Section 2. The secretary of state is hereby directed to transmit copies of this application to the
28 President and Secretary of the United States Senate and to the Speaker and Clerk of the United States House
